Autogrill Extends Airport Concession Contracts in U.S.

-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 
2011-06-08T10:32:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/autogrill-extends-airport-concession-contracts-in-u-s-correct-.html
(Corrects total annual revenue expected to $45 million.)  Autogrill SpA (AGL) , the world’s biggest
manager of airport and highway restaurants, extended two food-
and-beverage and retail concessions at  Salt Lake City  and a
contract at Port Columbus Airport, according to a statement
through the Italian exchange today.  The contracts are expected to generate annual revenues of
about $45 million overall “once they reach capacity,”
according to the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Bertacche at 
 mbertacche@bloomberg.net  